# GENESIS v5 - User Guide

## System Overview
GENESIS is now an autonomous agent running on Google Cloud Run.
- **Brain**: Gemini 3.0 Pro Preview (Planning & Chat)
- **Hands**: Gemini 2.5 Flash (Coding & Execution)
- **URL**: `https://genesis-brain-160983561198.us-central1.run.app`

## How to Operate
You do not interact with the Cloud Run URL directly. Instead, you communicate via GitHub (or local file simulation for now).

### 1. Give a Directive
Edit [genesis-monorepo/commands/user_directives.md](file:///c:/Users/puchi/Desktop/antigravity/genesis-monorepo/commands/user_directives.md):

```markdown
# GENESIS User Directives

- [ ] Create: A simple landing page for a coffee shop.
```

### 2. Trigger the Agent
*Currently, since we don't have a real GitHub Webhook connected to localhost, you need to manually trigger the webhook or push to a real repo.*

**Manual Trigger (PowerShell):**
```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "https://genesis-brain-160983561198.us-central1.run.app/webhook" -Method Post -ContentType "application/json" -Body '{"ref": "refs/heads/main", "commits": [{"modified": ["genesis-monorepo/commands/user_directives.md"]}]}'
```

### 3. Check Status
The agent will process your request and (in the future) update [reports/daily_status.md](file:///c:/Users/puchi/Desktop/antigravity/genesis-monorepo/reports/daily_status.md).
For now, you can check the Cloud Run logs in the GCP Console to see the "Brain" planning and "Hands" generating code.

## Next Steps
- Connect a real GitHub Repository to fully automate the webhook.
- Implement the file write-back logic (so the agent can actually save the generated code to the repo).
